<div id="review_1165763689" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1165763689" />
    <a title="Sarah Pianettini" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31760121-sarah-pianettini"><img alt="Sarah Pianettini" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483799027p2/31760121.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1165763689?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah Pianettini" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah Pianettini" href="/user/show/31760121-sarah-pianettini">Sarah Pianettini</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781508616535" href="/book/show/24443726-the-summer-remains">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1165763689" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2557957698731993519">I&apos;ve been sitting here for ten minutes and I don&apos;t know how to express how this book affected me. Sometimes when things really get to me emotionally I have trouble putting my feelings into words so please bare with me.<br/><br/>I&apos;ll start off by saying I&apos;ve never once doubted Seth&apos;s talent. From the second I started reading The Goode Fight I knew he was an amazing author. I also knew from the very first teaser that The Summer Remains would be off the charts amazing. What I did not expect was for Seth to c</span>
  <span id="freeText2557957698731993519" style="display:none">I've been sitting here for ten minutes and I don't know how to express how this book affected me. Sometimes when things really get to me emotionally I have trouble putting my feelings into words so please bare with me.<br /><br />I'll start off by saying I've never once doubted Seth's talent. From the second I started reading The Goode Fight I knew he was an amazing author. I also knew from the very first teaser that The Summer Remains would be off the charts amazing. What I did not expect was for Seth to come into my life, drop off Summer and Cooper and completely wreck me for any other books. Wreck. Me. I have the worst book hangover I've ever had. Not since reading The Lovely Bones, years ago, have I felt like this. <br />I usually hate female leads. I can never relate to them and they generally annoy the crap out of me. I fell in love with Summer on page one. So much so that when I would take a break from reading, I missed her. Missed. Her. That's huge for me. I can usually read a good book quick and move on. I found myself taking random breaks just so this book wouldn't be over. But when I would all I could think about was getting back to Summer and Cooper. I just wanted to jump into the book and have it never ever end. It's a weird feeling to not want to stop reading but not wanting the book to be over. <br /><br />The love story between Summer and Cooper is beautiful and tragic and wonderful. I can't put into words how it affected me. I really can't, I'm sorry.<br /><br />I cried, boy did I cry, but I also laughed and smiled a lot. I don't know what else to say that won't ruin this book for anyone. You really need to read and experience every second of this book for yourselves. It's a breathtakingly beautiful story that has truely dug it's way into my heart and will stay there forever. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2557957698731993519" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


