    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1169563696" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1169563696" />
    <a title="Beatriz Perez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7306377-beatriz-perez"><img alt="Beatriz Perez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1325471402p2/7306377.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1169563696?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beatriz Perez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beatriz Perez" href="/user/show/7306377-beatriz-perez">Beatriz Perez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781508616535" href="/book/show/24443726-the-summer-remains">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1169563696" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9789677604994220146">Forget everything and read this book!!<br/><br/>I started this book yesterday after I left work, and did not put it down till around 2am. The only break I took was to shower. I ate dinner, fork in my right hand and my kindle in my left hand. I HAD TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENED. The author has been posting all these teasers and I kept reading them like if I was in a desert and they were water. The moment the book was delivered to my kindle I&apos;m pretty sure I screamed. <br/><br/>Enough about me, lets get this review started. </span>
  <span id="freeText9789677604994220146" style="display:none">Forget everything and read this book!!<br /><br />I started this book yesterday after I left work, and did not put it down till around 2am. The only break I took was to shower. I ate dinner, fork in my right hand and my kindle in my left hand. I HAD TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENED. The author has been posting all these teasers and I kept reading them like if I was in a desert and they were water. The moment the book was delivered to my kindle I'm pretty sure I screamed. <br /><br />Enough about me, lets get this review started. <br /><br />Well, its really hard to put into words what this book made me feel. It's so incredibly well written I could feel all of the characters emotions. This is the first book I've read by this author and I can guarantee you, it will not be the last. The writing was just, God, flawless. The characters felt so real. With real issues, feelings, problems. And the love, WOW, I can't even describe it. <br /><br />Summer is 24 years old. She has a medical condition which will require surgery and most likely end her life. Her only wish before her surgery, is to fall in love. Her mom, doctor, and therapist are all against this idea. But if her life is ending, she is determined to experience love before this happens. She downloads a dating app where she meets Cooper Nichols. Gawd, Cooper!! I instantly liked him. <br /><br />After an awkward first date, they start seeing each other daily and they form a beautiful relationship. What Summer thought her namesake was going to be like, ends up being completely different once Cooper walks into the picture. These two characters meeting is fate. If there was ever a time I believed in soul mates, these two are the definition of it.<br /><br />There is a part in the book where Summer says she is shocked at the amount of affection that could flow between them, that they just <i>got</i> each other. And as you read the book you can feel that affection between them, that in itself, its amazing writing!! <br /><br />This is not your typical love story. Do not read this book expecting it, cause you'll be disappointed. This story is real, honest and devastatingly beautiful!! Everyday life, everyday people, with so much in common and at the same time so different. With damaged characters that will turn your world upside down and make you see your life with different eyes. I can't tell you this book hasn't changed me. I read it 12 hours ago, and it has already impacted my life. My heart still hurts for these characters. And I feel they will stay with me forever. <br /><br />Sorry for this scattered review. I don't even know if I'm making any sense at this point, but I don't know how to explain everything I'm still feeling about this amazing story. There are no words to explain it. You just have to experience it yourself. So please, do yourself a favor and get your copy of this book!! </span>
  <a data-text-id="9789677604994220146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

