<span id="freeTextContainer1371444038500273484"><br/>So….one thing you’ll learn about me is I’m a crier. Sometimes a book will make me tear up a little, sometimes it will make just a single tear fall in a lonely track down my cheek, but if the book really moves me, I’ve been known to be a big bumbling cry baby. If the author really does it right, I will sob, hiccup and get swollen red eyes. In other words: a full on ugly cry. Some of my book buds have been buzzing about this book lately so I was already thinking I should read it. Something kept ho</span>
  <span id="freeText1371444038500273484" style="display:none"><br />So….one thing you’ll learn about me is I’m a crier. Sometimes a book will make me tear up a little, sometimes it will make just a single tear fall in a lonely track down my cheek, but if the book really moves me, I’ve been known to be a big bumbling cry baby. If the author really does it right, I will sob, hiccup and get swollen red eyes. In other words: a full on ugly cry. Some of my book buds have been buzzing about this book lately so I was already thinking I should read it. Something kept holding me back, but I was finally intrigued enough to start it when my friend D (who is emphatically NOT a crier), told me she read this and it made even her tear up a little. But just a little mind you. For her this is HUGE! So out of curiosity I started reading......<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://straightshootinbookreviews.com/review-summer-remains-seth-king-2/">http://straightshootinbookreviews.com...</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
